<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/competition-appeal-tribunal> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The UK Competition Appeal Tribunal (CAT) is a specialist judicial body with a cross-disciplinary expertise in law, economics, business and accountancy, whose function is to hear and decide cases involving competition or economic regulatory issues. CAT is a tribunal of the Department for Business and Trade ."@en .
